Subject: [PATCH 3/4] Update registry target for GHCR publication

Based on kingdonb/cozystack commit ce8b1bb: "REGISTRY := kingdonb"
This changes the target registry from Docker Hub (kingdonb) to GHCR (urmanac) 
for the demo automation.

Changes:
- Update REGISTRY variable in common-envs.mk
- Target ghcr.io/urmanac namespace instead of kingdonb
- Maintain exact versioning pattern from manual builds
- Ensure ARM64 images published to correct registry

---
 scripts/common-envs.mk | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/scripts/common-envs.mk b/scripts/common-envs.mk
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/scripts/common-envs.mk
+++ b/scripts/common-envs.mk
@@ -1,4 +1,4 @@
-REGISTRY := kingdonb
+REGISTRY := ghcr.io/urmanac
 TAG ?= $(shell git describe --tags --abbrev=0 2>/dev/null || echo "latest")
 
 # Function to determine image tag